Got it working (thanks Milind Agrawal) with some edits :

    const includesName = (name = &#39;&#39;) =&gt; name.toLowerCase().includes(search);

    let filteredData = _.filter(data, data =&gt; {
        const { children, name } = data;
        return (
            !_.isEmpty(children)
                ? (
                    !!_.filter(children, ({ name }) =&gt; includesName(name)).length ||
                    includesName(name)
                )
                : includesName(name)
        );
    });

In the ternary we&#39;ll check if the parent has the value too + checking for the children-filtered results length (doesn&#39;t work without it)

if you are still interested in deepdash solution [here is an example](https://codepen.io/yurigor/pen/RwbEpGM?editors=0010) for your case:

